# Code with Haider

## Overview
Welcome to **Code with Haider**! This is a personal portfolio and timeline website showcasing the career journey and projects of Haider Ali, a senior frontend engineer.

## Features
- Responsive design
- Timeline of experience at companies like Shopify, Ambrook, Stripe, and Apple
- Clean and minimal UI
- Styled using CSS

## Installation

### Prerequisites
Make sure you have the following installed:
- [Node.js](https://nodejs.org/)
- [Yarn](https://yarnpkg.com/)

### Steps
1. Clone the repository:
   ```sh
   git clone https://github.com/your-username/code-with-haider.git
   ```
2. Navigate to the project folder:
   ```sh
   cd code-with-haider
   ```
3. Install dependencies:
   ```sh
   yarn install
   ```
4. Start the development server:
   ```sh
   yarn dev
   ```

## Deployment
The project can be deployed using [Vercel](https://vercel.com/).

1. Install Vercel CLI:
   ```sh
   npm install -g vercel
   ```
2. Deploy:
   ```sh
   vercel
   ```

## GitHub Setup
1. Initialize Git (if not already initialized):
   ```sh
   git init
   ```
2. Add a remote repository:
   ```sh
   git remote add origin https://github.com/your-username/code-with-haider.git
   ```
3. Commit and push changes:
   ```sh
   git add .
   git commit -m "Initial commit"
   git push -u origin main
   ```

